description.formattedDefault: These checks highlight opportunities to [improve the accessibility of your web app](https://web.dev/lighthouse-accessibility/). Only a subset of accessibility issues can be automatically detected so manual testing is also encouraged.

manualDescription.formattedDefault: These items address areas which an automated testing tool cannot cover. Learn more in our guide on [conducting an accessibility review](https://web.dev/how-to-review/).

description.formattedDefault: These checks ensure that your page is following basic search engine optimization advice. There are many additional factors Lighthouse does not score here that may affect your search ranking, including performance on [Core Web Vitals](https://web.dev/learn-web-vitals/). [Learn more](https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/35769).

manualDescription.formattedDefault: Run these additional validators on your site to check additional SEO best practices.

description.formattedDefault: These checks validate the aspects of a Progressive Web App. [Learn more](https://web.dev/pwa-checklist/).

manualDescription.formattedDefault: These checks are required by the baseline [PWA Checklist](https://web.dev/pwa-checklist/) but are not automatically checked by Lighthouse. They do not affect your score but it's important that you verify them manually.

description.formattedDefault: These suggestions can help your page load faster. They don't [directly affect](https://web.dev/performance-scoring/) the Performance score.
Performance budgets set standards for the performance of your site.
More information about the performance of your application. These numbers don't [directly affect](https://web.dev/performance-scoring/) the Performance score.
These items highlight common accessibility best practices.
These are opportunities to improve the legibility of your content.
These are opportunities to improve the semantics of the controls in your application. This may enhance the experience for users of assistive technology, like a screen reader.
These are opportunities to improve keyboard navigation in your application.
These are opportunities to improve the usage of ARIA in your application which may enhance the experience for users of assistive technology, like a screen reader.
These are opportunities to improve the interpretation of your content by users in different locales.
These are opportunities to provide alternative content for audio and video. This may improve the experience for users with hearing or vision impairments.
These are opportunities to improve the experience of reading tabular or list data using assistive technology, like a screen reader.
Make sure your pages are mobile friendly so users dont have to pinch or zoom in order to read the content pages. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/search/mobile-sites/).
Format your HTML in a way that enables crawlers to better understand your apps content.
To appear in search results, crawlers need access to your app.
